{
  "message": "fuzz(btrfs-inode-ref): add 14 structured corpus seeds across all modes\n\nExisting corpus had 3 seeds (seed_truncated, seed_valid_pair,\nseed_valid_single) covering only the simplest shapes for each\nSeedPayload variant. The harness drives five payload-builder modes\nwith non-trivial cursor-byte semantics; without targeted seeds for\nthe boundary cases libfuzzer takes many runs to discover them.\n\nNew seeds cover:\n- Mode Raw: minimal valid (1 entry), 3 concatenated entries, 200-byte\n  long name, name_len=0 (parser InvalidField path), declared name\n  longer than payload (InsufficientData path), declared u16::MAX\n  (bounds check), valid prefix followed by truncated tail.\n- Mode ValidSingle: empty name (forces parser-rejection path),\n  bounded_name at the 64-byte cap.\n- Mode ValidPair: short + long name pair to traverse the boundary\n  between consecutive entries.\n- Mode TruncatedTail: trim selector that lands mid-name and an\n  aggressive trim that strips most of the payload.\n- Mode DeclaredTooLong: smallest (+1) and largest (+32) overshoots\n  produced by the selector.\n\nValidated by 21-second libfuzzer run: 17 corpus files load cleanly,\ncoverage rises from 327 (existing seeds) to 460 PCs, no crashes\nacross 2.5M executions. fuzz/Cargo.lock picks up an existing\nffs-btree dependency that was added to Cargo.toml in a prior commit\nbut never relocked.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
